This paper deals with Bayesian networks and model selection, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. The use of latent variables is also a common theme in machine learning, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses effective dimensions, which are related to information theory and compression, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. The use of large models and the need for computational feasibility suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories.
